<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include("partials/header") %>

<body class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
  <%- include("partials/nav") %>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <section class="rounded-xl p-8 border-slate-700">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2 text-green-400">How PixelPicks Works</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About PixelPicks</h1>

      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300">
        Right now everybody is bored, stressed, and presented with endless choices of games to play.
        Choosing the right game to spend hours of your time on can be a complex endeavor, and has many
        factors involved such as the cost, story, gameplay, art, and technical design.

        <br><br>PixelPicks uses a decision matrix with several criteria from 1 (worst) to
        10 (best) to find the game best for your next playthrough. Higher values correlate
        to a higher performance.
      </p>

     <hr class="my-6 border-1 border-slate-700">

     <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Decision Criteria</h1>

     <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-slate-300">
         The criteria by which PixelPicks judges games.
     </p>

     <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 mt-5">
      <% data.criteria.forEach(function(criterion) { %>
        <div class="border rounded-lg p-4 border-slate-600 bg-slate-900">
          <label for="<%= criterion.id %>" class="block font-semibold mb-1">
            <%= criterion.name %>
          </label>

          <p class="text-sm mb-2 text-slate-400">
            <%= criterion.description %>
          </p>
        </div>
      <% }); %>
    </div>

     <hr class="my-6 border-1 border-slate-700">

      <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
        This app should support two backend ranking methods: Weighted Sum and Weighted Product.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include("partials/footer") %>
</body>
</html>
